The first bicycle (or Bike) available in Vietnam was the Euro-Retro Little Free-Wheeler 1982. This type of bike was a lot of fun and quick until you crashed into a wall or hit a river. Fast forward to 1013 and there is still a lot of fun to be had. A lot has changed since 1982. You probably don’t remember but hey, its time for a history lesson, so here we go.

In 2013, the first hybrid bicycle was introduced to the Vietnamese main island and city of Phù quốc. The hybrid bicycle had plenty of room for the new and inexperienced, or that is what most people thought. The hybrid bike had auto gears and a set of disc break which helped mostly children stick to bicycles and new motorbike users take on two wheels! Despite the negative and light weight attitude, the hybrid bike was cool and still is a great introductory bike for all ages. Remember when a hybrid was a big thing and you rocked that joint to your best friend’s sleepover?
